parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Intrusion into Rear Tail Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion into the rear tail light assembly can cause the lights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the tail light assembly
dim or flickering lights
complete failure of the tail light
corrosion on the connector
and burning out of the light.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear View Camera and Infotainment System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the rear view camera and infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The rear view camera does not respond immediately
the navigation system is slow
the radio stations are erased when the car is turned on
and a rattling sound from the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the headrest and seat heating system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The headrest pops open while driving
and the seat heating system does not work properly when the vehicle is remote started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear "racetrack" tail light can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Water collects in the tail light assembly
causing the lights to short out or fail completely
leading to reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of critical functions, such as turn signals, wipers, and headlights, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water enters the electrical system
causing shorts
failures
or malfunctions of various components
including the fuel pump relay
blinker arm
and navigation system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the active head restraint can cause distraction, injury, or accidents, especially if it deploys unexpectedly while driving.
symptoms: The active head restraint deploys unexpectedly
causing a violent distraction
and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of the active head restraint system can cause physical harm, including whiplash, headaches, and potential accidents due to the sudden and unexpected movement of the headrest.
symptoms: The headrest deploys without warning
hitting the driver or passenger in the head or back
causing sudden forward movement
and potentially leading to accidents or near-misses. The headrest may not return to its normal position
and the plastic components may be broken.
